               <p>It appear'd by the Evidence, That the Prosecutor's House had been broken, and the Goods stolen, and that the China Ware was found in the Prisoner's Possession.</p>
               <p>The Prisoner pleaded, He selling old Clothes about the Street, met a Sailor, or a Man in a Sailor's Habit, who wanted to buy some Clothes he had to sell; and telling him, he was a Holland Trader, exchang'd the China-Ware for the Clothes; he called a Witness to prove this, and a great many appearing to his Reputation, who gave him the Character of a very honest Man, the Jury <rs id="t17300228-54-verdict269" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17300228-54-verdict269" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs> him.</p>
